						               													<description>Long Knives was a set of rules published by Greenfield Hobby Distributors and written by Jim Birdseye.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;They were a simple but effective set of rules that depicted Indian vs Cavalry actions in the old west.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;No counters came with the game as they were primarily printed with the use of miniatures in mind.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Catalogue Description.&amp;#10;Basic rules for skirmish warfare in the Old West, covering the period 1830-1898, with special emphasis on the post-Civil War era. Rules are based on tactical level engagement where miniatures will represent individual combatants, with a scale of 4 yards per inch and 20 seconds per turn. Historical background and designer notes round out this 28-page booklet, complete with charts and optional procedures for play. Requires a standard deck of cards, six-sided and percentile dice for play (not included).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
